{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":920,"text":"The great philosopher Aristotle said"},{"time":4840,"text":"if something doesn't exist,\nthere's no word for it,"},{"time":9320,"text":"and if there's no word for something,"},{"time":11800,"text":"that something doesn't exist."},{"time":14200,"text":"So when we talk about elections,"},{"time":16360,"text":"we in established democracies,\nwe know what we're talking about."},{"time":19960,"text":"We've got the words.\nWe have the vocabulary."},{"time":22080,"text":"We know what a polling station is."},{"time":24000,"text":"We know what a ballot paper is."},{"time":26840,"text":"But what about countries\nwhere democracy doesn't exist,"},{"time":31760,"text":"countries where there are\nno words to describe the concepts"},{"time":36080,"text":"that underpin a democratic society?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39560,"text":"I work in the field\nof electoral assistance,"},{"time":41880,"text":"so that's to say we assist"},{"time":44040,"text":"emerging democracies to organize"},{"time":46200,"text":"what is often their first elections."},{"time":49480,"text":"When people ask me what I do,"},{"time":50920,"text":"quite often I get this answer."},{"time":53360,"text":"\"Oh, so you're one of these people\nwho goes around the world"},{"time":57200,"text":"imposing Western democracy\non countries that can't handle it.\""},{"time":62480,"text":"Well, the United Nations\ndoes not impose anything on anybody."},{"time":67600,"text":"It really doesn't,"},{"time":68840,"text":"and also, what we do"},{"time":71240,"text":"is firmly anchored in the 1948\nUniversal Declaration of Human Rights,"},{"time":77560,"text":"Article 21, that says"},{"time":79680,"text":"that everybody should have the right\nto choose who governs them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"So that's the basis of the work."},{"time":85560,"text":"I specialize in public outreach."},{"time":88480,"text":"What does that mean? Another jargon."},{"time":90920,"text":"It actually means\ndesigning information campaigns"},{"time":94720,"text":"so that candidates and voters"},{"time":97160,"text":"who have never had the opportunity\nto participate or to vote"},{"time":101480,"text":"understand where, when, how to register;"},{"time":105240,"text":"where, when, how to vote;"},{"time":107480,"text":"why, why it is important to take part."},{"time":110560,"text":"So I'll probably devise a specific\ncampaign to reach out to women"},{"time":115040,"text":"to make sure that they can take part,"},{"time":117080,"text":"that they can be part of the process."},{"time":119400,"text":"Young people as well."},{"time":121280,"text":"All sorts of people."},{"time":122520,"text":"Handicapped people."},{"time":123960,"text":"We try to reach everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126800,"text":"And it's not always easy,\nbecause very often in this work,"},{"time":130280,"text":"I've noticed now over the years\nthat I've been doing it"},{"time":133440,"text":"that words are lacking,"},{"time":135880,"text":"and so what do you do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138120,"text":"Afghanistan."},{"time":140200,"text":"It's a country with\nhigh levels of illiteracy,"},{"time":142720,"text":"and the thing about that was,\nit was in 2005,"},{"time":146600,"text":"and we organized two elections\non the same day."},{"time":150600,"text":"The reason was because the logistics\nare so incredibly difficult,"},{"time":154840,"text":"it seemed to be more efficient to do that."},{"time":157120,"text":"It was,"},{"time":158360,"text":"but on the other hand,\nexplaining two elections instead of one"},{"time":162840,"text":"was even more complicated."},{"time":164360,"text":"So we used a lot of images,"},{"time":166720,"text":"and when it came to the actual ballot,"},{"time":170360,"text":"we had problems, because\nso many people wanted to take part,"},{"time":173480,"text":"we had 300 candidates for 52 seats"},{"time":178440,"text":"in the Wolesi Jirga,\nwhich is the parliamentary elections."},{"time":182000,"text":"And for the Provincial Council,\nwe had even more candidates."},{"time":185240,"text":"We had 330 for 54 seats."},{"time":188240,"text":"So talking about ballot design,"},{"time":191320,"text":"this is what the ballot looked like."},{"time":195600,"text":"It's the size of a newspaper."},{"time":197240,"text":"This was the Wolesi Jirga ballot --"},{"time":199426,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":200600,"text":"Yeah, and --"},{"time":203080,"text":"this was the Provincial Council ballot."},{"time":207400,"text":"Even more."},{"time":208720,"text":"So you see, we did use\na lot of symbols and things like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213680,"text":"And we had other problems\nin Southern Sudan."},{"time":218480,"text":"Southern Sudan was a very different story."},{"time":221240,"text":"We had so many people\nwho had never, of course, voted,"},{"time":224360,"text":"but we had extremely, extremely\nhigh levels of illiteracy,"},{"time":229120,"text":"very, very poor infrastructure."},{"time":230920,"text":"For example -- I mean, it's a country\nthe size of Texas, more or less."},{"time":235520,"text":"We had seven kilometers of paved roads,"},{"time":239280,"text":"seven kilometers in the whole country,"},{"time":241360,"text":"and that includes the tarmac\nwhere we landed the planes"},{"time":244520,"text":"in Juba Airport."},{"time":246080,"text":"So transporting electoral materials, etc.,"},{"time":249240,"text":"is exceedingly difficult."},{"time":251520,"text":"People had no idea\nabout what a box looked like."},{"time":256519,"text":"It was very complicated,"},{"time":258839,"text":"so using verbal communication\nwas obviously the way to go,"},{"time":262960,"text":"but there were 132 languages."},{"time":266800,"text":"So that was extremely challenging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270480,"text":"Then I arrived in Tunisia in 2011."},{"time":274360,"text":"It was the Arab Spring."},{"time":276040,"text":"A huge amount of hope was generated\nby that enormous movement"},{"time":280360,"text":"that was going on in the region."},{"time":281960,"text":"There was Libya,\nthere was Egypt, there was Yemen."},{"time":285120,"text":"It was an enormous, enormous\nhistorical moment."},{"time":288160,"text":"And I was sitting\nwith the election commission,"},{"time":290760,"text":"and we were talking\nabout various aspects of the election,"},{"time":294520,"text":"and I was hearing them using words\nthat I hadn't actually heard before,"},{"time":297880,"text":"and I'd worked with Iraqis,\nI'd worked with Jordanians, Egyptians,"},{"time":302120,"text":"and suddenly they were using these words,"},{"time":304560,"text":"and I just thought, \"This is strange.\""},{"time":306440,"text":"And what really gave rise to it\nwas this word \"observer.\""},{"time":309360,"text":"We were discussing election observers,"},{"time":311640,"text":"and the election commissioner\nwas talking about \"mulahiz\" in Arabic."},{"time":316480,"text":"This means \"to notice\"\nin a passive sort of sense,"},{"time":320600,"text":"as in, \"I noticed\nhe was wearing a light blue shirt.\""},{"time":324240,"text":"Did I go and check whether\nthe shirt was light blue or not?"},{"time":327960,"text":"That is the role of an election observer."},{"time":329960,"text":"It's very active, it's governed\nby all kinds of treaties,"},{"time":334040,"text":"and it has got\nthat control function in it."},{"time":336840,"text":"And then I got wind\nof the fact that in Egypt,"},{"time":339040,"text":"they were using this term \"mutabiâ€™,\"\nwhich means \"to follow.\""},{"time":342400,"text":"So we were now having\nfollowers of an election."},{"time":344720,"text":"So that's not quite right either,"},{"time":347320,"text":"because there is a term\nthat's already accepted and in use,"},{"time":350106,"text":"which was the word \"muraqib\"\nwhich means \"a controller.\""},{"time":353400,"text":"It's got that notion of control."},{"time":355560,"text":"So I thought, three words\nfor one concept. This is not good."},{"time":359320,"text":"And with our colleagues,\nwe thought perhaps it's our role"},{"time":362440,"text":"to actually help make sure\nthat the words are understood"},{"time":366520,"text":"and actually create a work of reference"},{"time":369680,"text":"that could be used across the Arab region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372360,"text":"And that's what we did."},{"time":373640,"text":"So together with these colleagues,"},{"time":375320,"text":"we launched the \"Arabic Lexicon\nof Electoral Terminology,\""},{"time":379320,"text":"and we worked\nin eight different countries."},{"time":382600,"text":"It meant actually defining 481 terms"},{"time":387200,"text":"which formed the basis\nof everything you need to know"},{"time":390080,"text":"if you're going to organize\na democratic election."},{"time":392880,"text":"And we defined these terms,"},{"time":394240,"text":"and we worked with the Arab colleagues"},{"time":396240,"text":"and came to an agreement\nabout what would be the appropriate word"},{"time":400040,"text":"to use in Arabic."},{"time":401640,"text":"Because the Arabic language is very rich,\nand that's part of the problem."},{"time":405920,"text":"But there are 22 countries\nthat speak Arabic,"},{"time":408920,"text":"and they use modern standard Arabic,"},{"time":413640,"text":"which is the Arabic\nthat is used across the whole region"},{"time":416520,"text":"in newspapers and broadcasts,"},{"time":419040,"text":"but of course, then from one country\nto the next in day to day language and use"},{"time":423970,"text":"it varies -- dialect, colloquialisms, etc."},{"time":427320,"text":"So that was another\nadded layer of complication."},{"time":429920,"text":"So in one sense you had the problem"},{"time":432440,"text":"that language wasn't\nfully ripe, if you like,"},{"time":436120,"text":"neologisms were coming up,\nnew expressions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439400,"text":"And so we defined all these terms,"},{"time":441080,"text":"and then we had\neight correspondents in the region."},{"time":444400,"text":"We submitted the draft to them,"},{"time":446320,"text":"they responded back to us."},{"time":447920,"text":"\"Yes, we understand the definition."},{"time":450560,"text":"We agree with it,"},{"time":452280,"text":"but this is what we say in our country.\""},{"time":455480,"text":"Because we were not going\nto harmonize or force harmonization."},{"time":459120,"text":"We were trying to facilitate\nunderstanding among people."},{"time":462640,"text":"So in yellow, you see\nthe different expressions in use"},{"time":467720,"text":"in the various countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"So this, I'm happy to say,\nit took three years to produce this"},{"time":473960,"text":"because we also finalized the draft\nand took it actually into the field,"},{"time":478320,"text":"sat with the election commissions\nin all these different countries,"},{"time":481487,"text":"debated and defined and refined the draft,"},{"time":484400,"text":"and finally published it\nin November 2014 in Cairo."},{"time":489440,"text":"And it's gone a long way.\nWe published 10,000 copies."},{"time":492720,"text":"To date, there's about 3,000 downloads\noff the internet in PDF form."},{"time":497960,"text":"I heard just recently from a colleague\nthat they've taken it up in Somalia."},{"time":501880,"text":"They're going to produce\na version of this in Somalia,"},{"time":504800,"text":"because there's nothing in Somalia at all."},{"time":506840,"text":"So that's very good to know."},{"time":509880,"text":"And this newly formed Arab Organization\nfor Electoral Management Bodies,"},{"time":514159,"text":"which is trying to professionalize"},{"time":517120,"text":"how elections are run in the region,"},{"time":519440,"text":"they're using it as well."},{"time":521559,"text":"And the Arab League have now\nbuilt up a pan-Arab observation unit,"},{"time":527520,"text":"and they're using it."},{"time":528800,"text":"So that's all really good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531440,"text":"However, this work of reference\nis quite high-pitched."},{"time":535280,"text":"It's complex, and a lot of the terms\nare quite technical,"},{"time":538200,"text":"so the average person probably doesn't\nneed to know at least a third of it."},{"time":542960,"text":"But the people of the Middle East"},{"time":545040,"text":"have been deprived of any form\nof what we know as civic education."},{"time":549560,"text":"It's part of our curriculum at school."},{"time":552360,"text":"It doesn't really exist\nin that part of the world,"},{"time":555480,"text":"and I feel it's really\nthe right of everybody"},{"time":557920,"text":"to know how these things work."},{"time":560040,"text":"And it's a good thing to think about\nproducing a work of reference"},{"time":564680,"text":"for the average person,"},{"time":566360,"text":"and bearing in mind that now"},{"time":568520,"text":"we have a basis to work with,"},{"time":570720,"text":"but also we have technology,"},{"time":572880,"text":"so we can reach out using telephone apps,"},{"time":577280,"text":"video, animation."},{"time":579440,"text":"There's all sorts of tools\nthat can be used now"},{"time":581760,"text":"to communicate these ideas to people"},{"time":584280,"text":"for the first time in their own language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588200,"text":"We hear a lot of misery\nabout the Middle East."},{"time":590480,"text":"We hear the chaos of war.\nWe hear terrorism."},{"time":593680,"text":"We hear about sectarianism\nand all this horrible negative news"},{"time":599240,"text":"that comes to us all the time."},{"time":600920,"text":"What we're not hearing is what are\nthe people, the everyday people, thinking?"},{"time":605800,"text":"What are they aspiring to?"},{"time":607960,"text":"Let's give them the means,\nlet's give them the words."},{"time":612480,"text":"The silent majority is silent"},{"time":614720,"text":"because they don't have the words."},{"time":617200,"text":"The silent majority needs to know."},{"time":620440,"text":"It is time to provide people\nwith the knowledge tools"},{"time":623480,"text":"that they can inform themselves with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626920,"text":"The silent majority\ndoes not need to be silent."},{"time":630080,"text":"Let's help them have a voice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632400,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}